See the INSTALL file for instructions on how to install BiqCrunch.

After you have installed BiqCrunch, you can solve any binary quadratic
problem specified in the LP file format as follows.

1. Create a BiqCrunch BC file from the LP file:

    $ tools/lp2bc.py example.lp > example.bc

2. Run BiqCrunch on the BC file:

    $ problems/generic/biqcrunch example.bc biq_crunch.param

The details of the execution of BiqCrunch will be stored in a file 
called example.bc.output. For more details, run BiqCrunch as follows:

    $ problems/generic/biqcrunch -v 1 example.bc biq_crunch.param

